---- speedup summary (Gemma, warm server vs llama-cli cold-start) ----

  P20 Lite:  ~25-60 s cold-start per call -> 3.3-8.0 s warm call   (~5-10x)
  Pixel 6:   unmeasured with llama-cli     -> 1.7-5.0 s warm call

  Shaped exactly as expected: the first call eats the ~25 s prompt-ingest
  cost once; every subsequent call hits the KV cache (cache_prompt=true)
  and runs only the novel tokens of the new "Now: <phrase> ->" line.

---- readiness check ----

  3rd call on Pixel 6 < 1 s?  NO -- 4.88 s.  Shorter phrases (jump, stop)
  do drop to 1.7-1.9 s once warm.  For the briefing's <1 s target, the
  shortest tokens cross that bar on Pixel 6 but the longer few-shot-
  anchored phrases sit in the 2-5 s band.  P20 Lite is slower by ~2x
  per phrase due to its weaker CPU; never crosses 1 s in this bench.

